quran[12]{c,v,t}:
  35,19,The blind (disbelievers) and the seeing (believers) are not alike
  35,20,nor the darkness (disbelief) and the light (belief)
  35,21,nor the shade and the sun’s heat
  35,22,"nor the living and the dead. Surely, Allah can make hear whom He wills, but you (O Muhammad) cannot make those hear who are in graves"
  35,23,You (O Muhammad) are not but a Warner
  35,24,"Surely! We have sent you (O Muhammad) with the truth as a bearer of good news, and as a Warner. And there was not a nation which did not have a Warner"
  35,25,"And if they deny you, so surely were those who came before. Their Messengers came to them with clear signs, with the Scriptures, and the light-giving book"
  35,26,"Then I seized those who disbelieved, and how terrible was My denial (punishment)"
  35,27,Don’t you see that Allah sends down rain from the sky and We produce therewith fruits of varying colors? Among the mountains there are streaks (paths) white and red of varying colors and very black
  35,28,"And likewise, men, beasts, and cattle have various colors. It is only those among His servants who have knowledge that fear Allah. Surely, Allah is All-Mighty, Forgiving"
  35,29,"Surely, those who recite the book of Allah (this Qur’an), establish prayer, and spend (in charity) out of what We have provided for them, secretly and openly, may hope for business (gain) that will never perish"
  35,30,"That He may pay them their rewards in full and give them more out of His Grace. Surely! He is forgiving, ready to appreciate (good deeds)"